I’ve not liked the idea of creating billboards at first, however, a little research on the internet and I’ve found out that digital billboards (which’s not the case) is really effective. I presume, then, that the old fashioned paper one will achieve the results in Ghana.

There are some concerns about the proposal’s impact:
1)	You’ve planed to create a proposal not knowing if it’ll be possible (the authorities may not permit it), therefore you’ll receive a funding for nothing;
2)	The place where you’ll install the billboard which is critical for the marketing effectiveness. Therefore, adding a reference on the proposal would be good;
3)	You’ve stated that one of the reasons why you’ve chosen the billboard is because there are some places around Ghana that has poor internet. Therefore, do you have this statistic? I’m asking this because you’ll put a QR code in the advertisement linking to a YouTube video. That being said, I’m wondering how effective this billboard gonna be. The sole view of the Billboard will be sufficient to create an impact?
I do think that tackling these issues might be good for the proposal, creating more reliability.
